text: Abdul Latif was a Bangladesh Awami League politician and the former Member of Parliament of Brahmanbaria-5. ==Career== Latif was a Mukti Bahini commander. He was elected to parliament from Brahmanbaria-5 as a Bangladesh Awami League candidate in 1996. He founded Nabinagar Pourashava and Nabinagar Mohila Degree College. He was the President of Nabinagar Upazila unit of Bangladesh Awami League. ==Death== Latif died on 17 November 2001. ==References== Category:Awami League politicians Category:2001 deaths Category:7th Jatiya Sangsad members
title: Abdul Latif (Bangladeshi politician)
